<emu-intro id="sec-intro">
  <h1><span class="secnum"></span>Intro<span class="utils"><span class="anchor"><a href="#sec-intro">#</a></span></span></h1>
  <p>Forward references to <emu-xref href="#sec-dfn"><a href="#sec-dfn">dfn</a></emu-xref> work.</p>
  <p>Also terms from ES6 are auto-linked: <emu-xref href="#sec-lexical-environments"><a href="http://www.ecma-international.org/ecma-262/6.0/index.html#sec-lexical-environments">Lexical Environment</a></emu-xref>, <emu-xref aoid="Completion"><a href="http://www.ecma-international.org/ecma-262/6.0/index.html#sec-completion-record-specification-type">Completion</a></emu-xref>, etc.</p>
</emu-intro>
<emu-clause id="sec-dfn">
  <h1><span class="secnum">1</span>dfn<span class="utils"><span class="anchor"><a href="#sec-dfn">#</a></span></span></h1>

  <p>The term  <dfn>dfn</dfn> means the dfn tag. Other mentions of dfn in this clause should not be auto-linked.</p>

  <emu-clause id="sec-dfn-subclause">
    <h1><span class="secnum">1.1</span>dfn subclause<span class="utils"><span class="anchor"><a href="#sec-dfn-subclause">#</a></span></span></h1>

    <p><emu-xref href="#sec-dfn"><a href="#sec-dfn">dfn</a></emu-xref> should be auto-linked here as well. The linking of <emu-xref href="#sec-dfn"><a href="#sec-dfn">dfn</a></emu-xref> is case sensitive. But the header shouldn't auto-link.</p>
  </emu-clause>

  <p>Also terms are auto-linked in algorithms. But not naked abstract ops!</p>

  <!-- these shouldn't autolink as they are under the same clause that defines the dfn -->
  <emu-alg><ol><li>Call the <emu-xref href="#sec-dfn"><a href="#sec-dfn">dfn</a></emu-xref> algorithm.</li><li>Do something great with <emu-xref href="#sec-dfn"><a href="#sec-dfn">dfn</a></emu-xref>.</li><li><emu-xref href="#sec-dfn"><a href="#sec-dfn">dfn</a></emu-xref> is now awesome.
  </li></ol></emu-alg>

  <emu-clause id="sec-dfn-autolink">
    <h1><span class="secnum">1.2</span>dfn autolink<span class="utils"><span class="anchor"><a href="#sec-dfn-autolink">#</a></span></span></h1>

    <!-- these should autolink -->
    <emu-alg><ol><li>Call the <emu-xref href="#sec-dfn"><a href="#sec-dfn">dfn</a></emu-xref> algorithm.</li><li>Do something great with <emu-xref href="#sec-dfn"><a href="#sec-dfn">dfn</a></emu-xref>.</li><li><emu-xref href="#sec-dfn"><a href="#sec-dfn">dfn</a></emu-xref> is now awesome.
    </li></ol></emu-alg>
  </emu-clause>
</emu-clause>

<p><emu-xref href="#sec-dfn"><a href="#sec-dfn">dfn</a></emu-xref> is not auto-linked outside of clauses. Nor are terms created, such as <dfn>linking</dfn>.</p>
</body>